<script src="https://assets.crowd.aws/crowd-html-elements.js"></script>

<style>
  .key-phrase {
    color: green;
  }
</style>

<crowd-entity-annotation
  name="key-phrases"
  header="Highlight the key phrases andwords in the text below"
  labels="[{'label': 'keyPhrase', 'shortDisplayName': 'KP', 'longDisplayName': 'Key Phrase'}]"
  text="{{ task.input.taskObject }}"
>
  <short-instructions>
    <p>In the provided text, identify the key phrases. For example, the key phases are <span class="key-phrase">highlighted</span> in the following:</p>
    <p>"<span class="key-phrase">Excellent bag</span> and
        <span class="key-phrase">fast shipping</span>! Bag
        <span class="key-phrase">arrived right on time</span> and
        <span class="key-phrase">packaged very well</span>. The bag itself is
        <span class="key-phrase">good quality</span>! Was a bit
        <span class="key-phrase">skeptical</span> ordering this bag off amazon but it's
        <span class="key-phrase">100% authentic</span> and the
        <span class="key-phrase">best price</span>!"</p>
    <p>One way to help identify key phases is imagining what a word cloud would look like for this text.</p>
  </short-instructions>
  <full-instructions header="Key Phrase Exctraction instructions">
    Provide additional instructions and examples here
  </full-instructions>
</crowd-entity-annotation>